# Pivot wider: one column per sensor type
df_pivoted <- df_motorbelasting %>%
  pivot_wider(
    id_cols = c(MachineId, datekey, source_origin_id, MainGroupLabel, SubGroupLabel,
                BrandLabel, TypeOfEquipment, displayname_unique, Machinegroep,
                EngineClassificationLabel, ConstructionYear, Power),
    names_from  = SensorType,
    values_from = c(totalFuelPerDay, totalHoursPerDay, FPH, motorbelasting, countRows),
    values_fn   = list(
      totalFuelPerDay   = dplyr::first,
      totalHoursPerDay  = dplyr::first,
      FPH               = dplyr::first,
      motorbelasting    = dplyr::first,
      countRows         = dplyr::first
    ),
    names_sep = "_"
  )

# Consolidated fuel columns
df_pivoted$consolidated_fuel  <- NA_real_
df_pivoted$fuel_source        <- NA_character_

fuel_consumption_col <- "totalFuelPerDay_Fuel_consumption"
fuel_flow_col        <- "totalFuelPerDay_Fuel flow"
canbus_col           <- "totalFuelPerDay_CANBUS"

# Priority 1: Fuel_consumption
if (fuel_consumption_col %in% names(df_pivoted)) {
  mask <- !is.na(df_pivoted[[fuel_consumption_col]])
  df_pivoted$consolidated_fuel[mask] <- df_pivoted[[fuel_consumption_col]][mask]
  df_pivoted$fuel_source[mask]       <- "Fuel_consumption"
  cat("\n Applied Fuel_consumption for", sum(mask), "rows\n")
}

 Applied Fuel_consumption for 11010 rows
# Priority 2: Fuel flow
if (fuel_flow_col %in% names(df_pivoted)) {
  mask <- is.na(df_pivoted$consolidated_fuel) & !is.na(df_pivoted[[fuel_flow_col]])
  df_pivoted$consolidated_fuel[mask] <- df_pivoted[[fuel_flow_col]][mask]
  df_pivoted$fuel_source[mask]       <- "Fuel flow"
  cat(" Applied Fuel flow for", sum(mask), "rows\n")
}
 Applied Fuel flow for 2758 rows
# Priority 3: CANBUS
if (canbus_col %in% names(df_pivoted)) {
  mask <- is.na(df_pivoted$consolidated_fuel) & !is.na(df_pivoted[[canbus_col]])
  df_pivoted$consolidated_fuel[mask] <- df_pivoted[[canbus_col]][mask]
  df_pivoted$fuel_source[mask]       <- "CANBUS"
  cat(" Applied CANBUS for", sum(mask), "rows\n")
}
 Applied CANBUS for 14517 rows
# Helper: priority order
priority <- c("Fuel_consumption", "Fuel flow", "CANBUS")

# Consolidated hours
df_pivoted$consolidated_hours <- NA_real_
for (s in priority) {
  col_name <- paste0("totalHoursPerDay_", s)
  if (col_name %in% names(df_pivoted)) {
    mask <- is.na(df_pivoted$consolidated_hours) & !is.na(df_pivoted[[col_name]])
    df_pivoted$consolidated_hours[mask] <- df_pivoted[[col_name]][mask]
  }
}

# Consolidated motorbelasting
df_pivoted$consolidated_motorbelasting <- NA_real_
for (s in priority) {
  col_name <- paste0("motorbelasting_", s)
  if (col_name %in% names(df_pivoted)) {
    mask <- is.na(df_pivoted$consolidated_motorbelasting) & !is.na(df_pivoted[[col_name]])
    df_pivoted$consolidated_motorbelasting[mask] <- df_pivoted[[col_name]][mask]
  }
}

# Consolidated FPH
df_pivoted$consolidated_FPH <- NA_real_
for (s in priority) {
  col_name <- paste0("FPH_", s)
  if (col_name %in% names(df_pivoted)) {
    mask <- is.na(df_pivoted$consolidated_FPH) & !is.na(df_pivoted[[col_name]])
    df_pivoted$consolidated_FPH[mask] <- df_pivoted[[col_name]][mask]
  }
}

# Final clean dataframe
df_machine_day <- df_pivoted %>%
  select(
    MachineId, datekey, source_origin_id, displayname_unique,
    MainGroupLabel, SubGroupLabel, BrandLabel, TypeOfEquipment,
    Machinegroep, EngineClassificationLabel, ConstructionYear, Power,
    consolidated_fuel, consolidated_hours,
    consolidated_motorbelasting, consolidated_FPH, fuel_source
  ) %>%
  rename(
    fuel           = consolidated_fuel,
    hours          = consolidated_hours,
    motorbelasting = consolidated_motorbelasting,
    FPH            = consolidated_FPH
  )

cat("\n", strrep("=", 60), "\n", sep = "")

============================================================
cat("Final dataframe shape: ", paste(dim(df_machine_day), collapse = " x "), "\n")
Final dataframe shape:  30431 x 17 
cat(strrep("=", 60), "\n")
============================================================ 
head(df_machine_day, 10)
df_machines <- df_machine_day %>%
  filter(motorbelasting<1) %>% 
  group_by(MachineId, displayname_unique, MainGroupLabel, SubGroupLabel, Machinegroep, EngineClassificationLabel, ConstructionYear, Power) %>% 
  summarise(hours=mean(hours),
            hoursSd=sd(hours),
            motorbelasting=mean(motorbelasting),
            motorbelastingSd=sd(motorbelasting),
            FPH=mean(FPH),
            FPHSd=sd(FPH))

`summarise()` has grouped output by 'MachineId', 'displayname_unique', 'MainGroupLabel', 'SubGroupLabel', 'Machinegroep', 'EngineClassificationLabel', 'ConstructionYear'. You can override using the `.groups` argument.
